      "name": "description",
      "value": "Systematically probe the three hypothesized methodological tradeoffs (pseudopotential transferability, basis-set convergence, XC-functional interaction) by running a small set of PAW vs. LAPW calculations on SrTiO₃ with varying O vacancy positions, comparing Ti 3d occupation, total energy differences, and semicore state relaxation."
    },
    {
      "@type": "PropertyValue",
      "name": "expected_prediction",
      "value": "The 0.3–0.8 eV discrepancy will correlate with Ti 3s/3p semicore eigenvalue shifts >0.2 eV between PAW and LAPW; the discrepancy will be largest when the vacancy is nearest-neighbor to Ti and smallest when next-nearest-neighbor; PBE will show larger discrepancy than HSE06 due to reduced self-interaction masking the semicore relaxation effect."
    },
